tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditional - Finished T79 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.curYearHigh: Made 11 starts on the Mackenzie Tour - PGA TOUR Canada and finished twice in the top 25...Shot weekend rounds of 69-68 at The Players Cup to finish T14...A second-round 65 at The Great Waterway Classic earned a T19 finish...Won the Florida Professional Tour's Indian River Open at New Smyrna Beach GC by one shot in February...Finished T4 at Florida's Q-School with rounds of 68-65-68-67.
tourBios.carHigh: Has not made a start on the Web.com Tour or PGA TOUR prior to the start of the 2014 season. Two-time winner on the Hooter NGA Carolina Series.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Member of Murray State's 2010 Ohio Valley Conference championship team.
tourBios.personal: Attended Butler High School in Louisville. Earliest golf memory came at age 2 with a plastic set of clubs. Took a club out, shot the ball and hit his father, who was behind the camera videotaping him...Says if he weren't a professional golfer, he'd be in law enforcement...Favorite courses he's played include TPC Sawgrass and Valhalla CC and would like to play Pebble Beach GL and Augusta National...Favorite gadgets include his iPhone and Xbox 360. Enjoys The Bible, Twitter, ESPN and Golf Channel apps...Favorite teams include the Louisville Cardinals, the Murray State Racers and the Denver Broncos...Enjoys watching "The Office," "Parks and Recreation," "Modern Family" and movies starring Will Ferrell and Vince Vaughn...Likes pizza and everything his wife cooks...Favorite cities include New York City, St. Petersburg, Fla., and Cancun, Mexico...Carries peanut butter sandwiches and nutrition bars in his golf bag for snacks...Would like to trade places with Dwyane Wade because he'd like to know what it feels like to dunk a basketball...Dream foursome would include Michael Jordan, Bill Murray and Adam Sandler...Likes listening to old music, especially Frank Sinatra...Bucket list includes going to Australia with his wife, flying in a fighter jet and driving a supercar...Involved with Fellowship of Christian Athletes...Would like to be featured in Victory Magazine for FCA and on the Food Network so that he could learn some cooking tips...Says he started playing golf because he couldn't jump high enough to play basketball and was too slow for other sports...Has one brother and one sister...Twitter account is @Jaredwolfepro.
